name: Dungeons of Death (Adventures in the Forgotten Realms Commander Precon Decklist)

main.name: Sefris of the Hidden Ways
main.oracle_text:
Whenever one or more creature cards are put into your graveyard from anywhere, venture into the dungeon. This ability triggers only once each turn. (To venture into the dungeon, enter the first room or advance to the next room.)
Create Undead — Whenever you complete a dungeon, return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.

card.name: Swamp
card.flavor_text: You expected to meet hostile drow in this ancient ruin . . . but they fled long ago. What darkness could have driven them out?

card.name: Plains
card.flavor_text: Venturing beneath the desert sands, you've discovered an alien power pulsing with inconceivable energy.

card.name: Island
card.flavor_text: In crystal-studded waters far below the surface, you've discovered an incubating egg of mysterious origin.

card.name: Evolving Wilds
card.oracle_text: {T}, Sacrifice Evolving Wilds: Search your library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text: Parts of Faerûn still churn with the magic of arrogant Netherese archmages long dead.

card.name: Dungeon Map
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{3}, {T}: Venture into the dungeon. Activate only as a sorcery. (Enter the first room or advance to the next room.)
card.flavor_text: "Wait, is that a secret door? I can't tell for sure . . . there's some blood in the way."

card.name: Hama Pashar, Ruin Seeker
card.oracle_text: Room abilities of dungeons you own trigger an additional time.
card.flavor_text: "Someone took the time to carve these inscriptions. The least we can do is care enough to read them."

card.name: Minimus Containment
card.oracle_text:
Enchant nonland permanent
Enchanted permanent is a Treasure artifact with "{T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Add one mana of any color," and it loses all other abilities. (If it was a creature, it's no longer a creature.)

card.name: Bucknard's Everfull Purse
card.oracle_text: {1}, {T}: Roll a d4 and create a number of Treasure tokens equal to the result. The player to your right gains control of Bucknard's Everfull Purse.
card.flavor_text: As long as it's never left empty, this magic pouch produces coins every dawn.

card.name: Clay Golem
card.oracle_text:
{6}, Roll a d8: Monstrosity X, where X is the result. (If this creature isn't monstrous, put X +1/+1 counters on it and it becomes monstrous.)
Berserk — When Clay Golem becomes monstrous, destroy target permanent.

card.name: Thorough Investigation
card.oracle_text:
Whenever you attack, investigate. (Create a Clue token. It's an artifact with "{2}, Sacrifice this artifact: Draw a card.")
Whenever you sacrifice a Clue, venture into the dungeon. (Enter the first room or advance to the next room.)

card.name: Minn, Wily Illusionist
card.oracle_text:
Whenever you draw your second card each turn, create a 1/1 blue Illusion creature token with "This creature gets +1/+0 for each other Illusion you control."
Whenever an Illusion you control dies, you may put a permanent card with mana value less than or equal to that creature's power from your hand onto the battlefield.

card.name: Midnight Pathlighter
card.oracle_text:
Creatures you control can't be blocked except by legendary creatures.
Whenever one or more creatures you control deal combat damage to a player, venture into the dungeon. (Enter the first room or advance to the next room.)

card.name: Radiant Solar
card.oracle_text:
Flying, lifelink
Whenever Radiant Solar or another nontoken creature you control enters, venture into the dungeon. (Enter the first room or advance to the next room.)
{W}, Discard Radiant Solar: Venture into the dungeon and you gain 3 life.

card.name: Rod of Absorption
card.oracle_text:
Whenever a player casts an instant or sorcery spell, exile it instead of putting it into a graveyard as it resolves.
{X}, {T}, Sacrifice Rod of Absorption: You may cast any number of spells from among cards exiled with Rod of Absorption with total mana value X or less without paying their mana costs.

card.name: Revivify
card.oracle_text:
Roll a d20 and add the number of creature cards in your graveyard that were put there from the battlefield this turn.
1—14 | Return all creature cards in your graveyard that were put there from the battlefield this turn to your hand.
15+ | Return those cards from your graveyard to the battlefield.

card.name: Immovable Rod
card.oracle_text:
You may choose not to untap Immovable Rod during your untap step.
Whenever Immovable Rod becomes untapped, venture into the dungeon.
{3}{W}, {T}: For as long as Immovable Rod remains tapped, another target permanent loses all abilities and can't attack or block.

card.name: Phantom Steed
card.oracle_text:
Flash
When Phantom Steed enters, exile another target creature you control until Phantom Steed leaves the battlefield.
Whenever Phantom Steed attacks, create a tapped and attacking token that's a copy of the exiled card, except it's an Illusion in addition to its other types. Sacrifice that token at end of combat.

card.name: Component Pouch
card.oracle_text:
{T}, Remove a component counter from Component Pouch: Add two mana of different colors.
{T}: Roll a d20.
1—9 | Put a component counter on Component Pouch.
10—20 | Put two component counters on Component Pouch.

card.name: Extract Brain
card.oracle_text: Target opponent chooses X cards from their hand. Look at those cards. You may cast a spell from among them without paying its mana cost.
card.flavor_text: No thought is as succulent as a secret.

card.name: Grave Endeavor
card.oracle_text: Roll two d10 and choose one result. Return a creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield with a number of +1/+1 counters on it equal to that result. Then each opponent loses X life and you gain X life, where X is the other result.
card.flavor_text: Not alive, not dead, but definitely furious.

card.name: Wand of Orcus
Arcane Endeavor
card.oracle_text: Roll two d8 and choose one result. Draw cards equal to that result. Then you may cast an instant or sorcery spell with mana value less than or equal to the other result from your hand without paying its mana cost.
card.flavor_text: Late at night, when dreams touch a studious mind, bouts of inspiration strike.

card.name: Sol Ring
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add {C}{C}.
card.flavor_text: Lost to time is the artificer's art of trapping light from a distant star in a ring of purest gold.

card.name: Arcane Sanctum
card.oracle_text:
Arcane Sanctum enters tapped.
{T}: Add {W}, {U}, or {B}.
card.flavor_text:
"We must rely on our own knowledge, not on the dogma of the seekers or the mutterings of the sphinxes."
—Tullus of Palandius

card.name: Ashen Rider
card.oracle_text:
Flying
When Ashen Rider enters or dies, exile target permanent.
card.flavor_text: One offering to appease her on her arrival. Another to celebrate her departure.

card.name: Azorius Chancery
card.oracle_text:
Azorius Chancery enters tapped.
When Azorius Chancery enters, return a land you control to its owner's hand.
{T}: Add {W}{U}.

card.name: Baleful Strix
card.oracle_text:
Flying, deathtouch
When Baleful Strix enters, draw a card.
card.flavor_text: Its beak rends flesh and bone, exposing the tender marrow of dream.

card.name: Arcane Signet
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
card.flavor_text: It started as a mere drop of water. The Magic Mirror crystallized it into much more.

card.name: Burnished Hart
card.oracle_text: {3}, Sacrifice Burnished Hart: Search your library for up to two basic land cards, put them onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text: Forged by divine hands to wander mortal realms.

card.name: Cataclysmic Gearhulk
card.oracle_text:
Vigilance
When Cataclysmic Gearhulk enters, each player chooses an artifact, a creature, an enchantment, and a planeswalker from among the nonland permanents they control, then sacrifices the rest.

card.name: Champion of Wits
card.oracle_text:
When Champion of Wits enters, you may draw cards equal to its power. If you do, discard two cards.
Eternalize {5}{U}{U} ({5}{U}{U}, Exile this card from your graveyard: Create a token that's a copy of it, except it's a 4/4 black Zombie Snake Wizard with no mana cost. Eternalize only as a sorcery.)

card.name: Choked Estuary
card.oracle_text:
As Choked Estuary enters, you may reveal an Island or Swamp card from your hand. If you don't, Choked Estuary enters tapped.
{T}: Add {U} or {B}.

card.name: Cloudblazer
card.oracle_text:
Flying
When Cloudblazer enters, you gain 2 life and draw two cards.
card.flavor_text: All the aether charts in the world can't compete with the trained eye of a talented scout.

card.name: Commander's Sphere
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
Sacrifice Commander's Sphere: Draw a card.
card.flavor_text: "The heavens augur weal . . . for me. Woe for you."

card.name: Curator of Mysteries
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Whenever you cycle or discard another card, scry 1.
Cycling {U} ({U}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
card.flavor_text: To consult a sphinx is a test in patience. Perhaps that's the point.

card.name: Command Tower
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
card.flavor_text:
"Approach my tower on bended knee or depart from it as ash upon the wind."
—Gadwick, the Wizened

card.name: Darkwater Catacombs
card.flavor_text: Underdark flooding has swallowed ancient drow burial chambers, which are now haunted . . . and infested with oozes.

card.name: Despark
card.oracle_text: Exile target permanent with mana value 4 or greater.
card.flavor_text: Liliana whispered to whatever consciousness Oketra and Bontu had left. "You are the gods. He is the usurper. You know what to do."

card.name: Dimir Aqueduct
card.oracle_text:
Dimir Aqueduct enters tapped.
When Dimir Aqueduct enters, return a land you control to its owner's hand.
{T}: Add {U}{B}.

card.name: Doomed Necromancer
card.oracle_text: {B}, {T}, Sacrifice Doomed Necromancer: Return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.
card.flavor_text: Many necromancers share the same last words—the ones that conclude the undeath ritual.

card.name: Esper Panorama
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{1}, {T}, Sacrifice Esper Panorama: Search your library for a basic Plains, Island, or Swamp card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text: Esper is an expansive canvas painted by precise, controlling hands.

card.name: Eternal Dragon
card.oracle_text:
Flying
{3}{W}{W}: Return Eternal Dragon from your graveyard to your hand. Activate only during your upkeep.
Plainscycling {2} ({2}, Discard this card: Search your library for a Plains card, reveal it, put it into your hand, then shuffle.)

card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color that a land an opponent controls could produce.
card.flavor_text:
"It was a strange morning. When we awoke, we found our trees transformed. We didn't know whether to water them or polish them."
—Pulan, Bant orchardist

card.name: Fellwar Stone
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color that a land an opponent controls could produce.
card.flavor_text:
"What do you have that I cannot obtain?"
—Mairsil, the Pretender

card.name: Forbidden Alchemy
card.oracle_text:
Look at the top four cards of your library. Put one of them into your hand and the rest into your graveyard.
Flashback {6}{B} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

card.name: Geier Reach Sanitarium
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{2}, {T}: Each player draws a card, then discards a card.
card.flavor_text: All are welcome.

card.name: High Market
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{T}, Sacrifice a creature: You gain 1 life.
card.flavor_text: If it can't be had here, it can't be had on any world.

card.name: Hostage Taker
card.oracle_text: When Hostage Taker enters, exile another target creature or artifact until Hostage Taker leaves the battlefield. You may cast that card for as long as it remains exiled, and mana of any type can be spent to cast that spell.

card.name: Karmic Guide
card.oracle_text:
Flying, protection from black
Echo {3}{W}{W} (At the beginning of your upkeep, if this came under your control since the beginning of your last upkeep, sacrifice it unless you pay its echo cost.)
When Karmic Guide enters, return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.

card.name: Lightning Greaves
card.oracle_text:
Equipped creature has haste and shroud. (It can't be the target of spells or abilities.)
Equip {0}
card.flavor_text: After lightning struck the cliffs, the ore became iron, the iron became steel, and the steel became greaves. The lightning never left.

card.name: Mulldrifter
card.oracle_text:
Flying
When Mulldrifter enters, draw two cards.
Evoke {2}{U} (You may cast this spell for its evoke cost. If you do, it's sacrificed when it enters.)

card.name: Murder of Crows
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Whenever another creature dies, you may draw a card. If you do, discard a card.
card.flavor_text: Even more than carrion, they crave the last words of the dying.

card.name: Merfolk Looter
card.oracle_text: {T}: Draw a card, then discard a card.
card.flavor_text: Merfolk don't always know what they're looking for, but they're certain once they find it.

card.name: Necromantic Selection
card.oracle_text: Destroy all creatures, then return a creature card put into a graveyard this way to the battlefield under your control. It's a black Zombie in addition to its other colors and types. Exile Necromantic Selection.
card.flavor_text: It shambled from the cloud of ash and bone dust, undeterred by its own extinction.

card.name: Necrotic Sliver
card.oracle_text: All Slivers have "{3}, Sacrifice this permanent: Destroy target permanent."
card.flavor_text: Though Volrath is long dead, the slivers have become everything he wanted them to be: mindless instruments of destruction and despair.

card.name: Nimbus Maze
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{T}: Add {W}. Activate only if you control an Island.
{T}: Add {U}. Activate only if you control a Plains.
card.flavor_text: To find its center is to find one's own.

card.name: Obsessive Stitcher
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Draw a card, then discard a card.
{2}{U}{B}, {T}, Sacrifice Obsessive Stitcher: Return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.
card.flavor_text: No one is as dedicated to perfection as a stitcher working on their latest masterpiece.

card.name: Meteor Golem
card.oracle_text: When Meteor Golem enters, destroy target nonland permanent an opponent controls.
card.flavor_text: The impact sent the soldiers scattering—then something came out of the crater.

card.name: Orzhov Basilica

Orzhov Basilica enters tapped.
When Orzhov Basilica enters, return a land you control to its owner's hand.
{T}: Add {W}{B}.

card.oracle_text: You may have Phantasmal Image enter as a copy of any creature on the battlefield, except it's an Illusion in addition to its other types and it has "When this creature becomes the target of a spell or ability, sacrifice it."

card.name: Plaguecrafter
card.oracle_text: When Plaguecrafter enters, each player sacrifices a creature or planeswalker. Each player who can't discards a card.
card.flavor_text: "My power is generosity, in a way. I give my survivors an appreciation for their lives."

card.name: Port Town
card.oracle_text:
As Port Town enters, you may reveal a Plains or Island card from your hand. If you don't, Port Town enters tapped.
{T}: Add {W} or {U}.

card.oracle_text:
({T}: Add {W} or {U}.)
Prairie Stream enters tapped unless you control two or more basic lands.
card.flavor_text: The continent of Ondu is a vast plateau crisscrossed by deep trenches and meandering rivers.

card.name: Propaganda
card.oracle_text: Creatures can't attack you unless their controller pays {2} for each creature they control that's attacking you.
card.flavor_text:
"The cost of your opposition will be extracted from your wits."
—Nekusar, the Mindrazer

card.name: Reassembling Skeleton
card.oracle_text: {1}{B}: Return Reassembling Skeleton from your graveyard to the battlefield tapped.
card.flavor_text:
"They may show up with the wrong thigh bone or mandible, but they always show up."
—Zul Ashur, lich lord

card.name: Ronom Unicorn
card.oracle_text: Sacrifice Ronom Unicorn: Destroy target enchantment.
card.flavor_text: The aberrant magic of the Rimewind drew the unicorns back from the northern wastes to do battle once again.

card.name: Shriekmaw

Fear (This creature can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)

card.oracle_text:

card.oracle_text:

({T}: Add {U} or {B}.)

card.flavor_text: Take two steps north into the unsettled future, south into the unquiet past, east into the present day, or west into the great unknown.

card.name: Swords to Plowshares
card.oracle_text: Exile target creature. Its controller gains life equal to its power.
card.flavor_text: The smallest seed of regret can bloom into redemption.

Thriving Moor enters tapped. As it enters, choose a color other than black.
{T}: Add {B} or one mana of the chosen color.
card.flavor_text: Beauty appears in strange places for those with eyes to see it.

card.oracle_text:
Return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.
Flashback {3}{W} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)
card.flavor_text: All crave the Blessed Sleep. Few receive it.

card.name: Utter End
card.oracle_text: Exile target nonland permanent.
card.flavor_text:

card.flavor_text:
